        "username": "CarstenW",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/carstenw/{size}/52354_2.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-10T13:31:41.073Z",
        "cooked": "<p>As first workaround it should be possible to not only change the color of the message-bubbles for sent messages, but also the bubbles for received messages. But in the long term, the default color-scheme should be switched to better accessibility by default.</p>\n<p>Maybe there should also be an option for group-chats to give the received messages a frame in the color that is assigned to the sender.</p>",
