        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/ccd318/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2026-01-10T13:59:22.954Z",
        "cooked": "<p>It actually used to work like that, as far as I remember. You used to be able to chose a colour for a contact and the incoming mesaages would have that colour background. The outgoing messages used to be grey. As you can see here:</p>\n<aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\" data-onebox-src=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20210226005144/https://signal.org/\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n      <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/a/c/ac7157e2a0926cd55e4927a03e00c4d1223c4e91.png\" class=\"site-icon\" alt=\"\" data-dominant-color=\"8CAFF6\" width=\"192\" height=\"192\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20210226005144/https://signal.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Signal Messenger</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"aspect-image\" style=\"--aspect-ratio:690/361;\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/4/9/4909f66cf45ef551cb253cdbb243ac33a241408f_2_690x362.png\" class=\"thumbnail\" alt=\"\" data-dominant-color=\"EAEDF2\" width=\"690\" height=\"362\"></div>\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20210226005144/https://signal.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Signal Messenger: Speak Freely</a></h3>\n\n  <p>Say \"hello\" to a different messaging experience. An unexpected focus on privacy, combined with all of the features you expect.</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n\n<p>The same went for groups. I think, the colours in groups even used to match the contact’s colour you had chosen.</p>\n<p>I’ve always kinda missed this, so I think it would be nice if it came back. It could also allow for changing the incoming messages to be black on white.</p>",
